'''George A. Best''' was an English [[association footballer|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. He played professionally for [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in the early 20th century, either side of spells with his hometown club, [[Worksop Town F.C.|Worksop Town]].

Best made his debut for Blackpool just over halfway through the [[1925–26 Blackpool F.C. season|1925–26]] season, as deputy for [[Len Crompton]], in a 5–2 defeat at Derby County. He appeared in the two successive games — a 3–0 home victory over Bradford City and a 5–0 reversal at Port Vale — before Crompton returned to the line-up.

The following [[1926–27 Blackpool F.C. season|1926–27]] campaign saw Best make 24 [[Football League|League]] appearances. He played his final game for the club on 18 April, in a 2–2 draw at South Shields.

